## How to Sync This Project

This project is managed by Product-Spec-Agent. The files in this handoff are a
snapshot of the current product context, implementation guidance, decisions,
clarifications, tasks, and supporting documents at export time.

When you need the latest project state, refresh the handoff package from the
service:

```bash
curl -L -o handoff.zip "{{{syncUrl}}}"
unzip -o handoff.zip
rm handoff.zip
```

- **Sync-URL:** `{{{syncUrl}}}`
- **Method:** `GET` (no auth, no request body)
- **Response:** ZIP archive with the current handoff files.

## IMPORTANT: Start With `handoff-setup` skill

After syncing, use the bundled `handoff-setup` skill before planning or coding.
It turns `SPEC.md`, `implementation-order.md`, feature docs, tasks, decisions,
and clarifications into an interactive MVP selection with the user.

- **Skill:** `handoff-setup`
- **Path:** `.claude/skills/global.product-spec-sync/handoff-setup/SKILL.md`
- **Fallback:** If your agent cannot load skills, follow the workflow in that file manually with `docs/spec.md`.

Before any substantial change, refresh the handoff package and inspect what
changed. Compare the refreshed files with your local work before editing, so
you do not overwrite newer product context.
